text.section:
If bids are solicited from exhibitors for the purpose of entering into a license agreement, the invitation to bid shall specify:
Whether the run for which the bid is solicited is a first, second or subsequent run; whether the run is an exclusive or nonexclusive run; and the geographic area for the run;
The names of all exhibitors who are being solicited;
The date and hour the invitation to bid expires; and
The time, date and the location, including the address, where the bids will be opened, which shall be within the state.
